         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Robert St Brisbane ¶ Oct 11th 1878 ¶ Baron von Mueller ¶ My dear Sir ¶  ¶ Let me hope that long before this can reach you that you will have recovered from your sad sickness. I have just received a le...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">78.10.11a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Frederick Bailey</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M5, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Robert St Brisbane</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Oct 11th 1878</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Baron von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me hope that long before this can reach you that you will have recovered from your sad sickness. I have just received a letter from the Palmer<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Palmer River, Qld.</p>
               </note> stating that the lemon scented Ironbark is not yet in flower but that as soon as it does flower I shall receive some specimens which I shall of course send to you I send by todays post a few either new things or new for habitats<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In his notebook (</seg>Notebook, Colonial Botanist, Queensland Herbarium, Brisbane)<seg style="">, Bailey recorded under this date, ‘</seg>Baron Mueller sent specimens of a new form of Daviesia corymbosa Sm or a new species from Eight Mile Plane [Qld] Also Acacia hispidula Willd. &amp; Notelaea ovata from same place’.</p>
               </note> hoping to hear soon your obliged</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">F. M. Bailey</p>
         </div>
      </body>
